This phase II trial studies the effects of interstitial photodynamic therapy in patients with head and neck cancer that has come back.

 Interstitial photodynamic therapy uses a combination of laser light and a light-sensitive drug called porfimer sodium to destroy tumors.

 During treatment a laser light is used to activate the drug.

 Interstitial photodynamic therapy may be an effective treatment for head and neck cancer.

